President Muhammadu Buhari has reacted to the death of Mrs. Tola Oyediran, eldest daughter of nationalist, Chief Obafemi Awolowo. Buhari sent his condolences to the family of the late Premier of the Western Region over the death. In a statement signed by Garba Shehu and made available to DAILY POST on Friday, Buhari commiserated with friends and associates of the departed particularly Mrs. Tokunbo Awolowo, Oyediran’s only surviving sister The President wants Oyediran’s family to take solace in her investments of making life better for others. The President prayed that God will accept the soul of the departed, and comfort all her loved ones.